<name>SEAT BELT WARNING SYSTEM</name>
<para id="RM0000014DK00BX" category="J" type-id="3017V" name-id="SB0MZ-01" from="200601">
<dtccode/>
<dtcname>Driver Side Seat Belt Warning Light does not Operate</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM0000014DK00BX_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00007Y700000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>When the ignition switch is on (IG), the center airbag sensor assembly transmits front seat inner belt state signals to the combination meter assembly through CAN. If the driver seat belt is not fastened, the combination meter assembly blinks the driver seat belt warning light. If the seat belt is fastened, the warning light goes off.</ptxt>
<atten3>
<ptxt>The seat belt warning system uses CAN. Before troubleshooting the seat belt warning system, perform "COMMUNICATION FUNCTION CHECK" by following "HOW TO PROCEED WITH TROUBLESHOOTING" to confirm that the communication systems are normal.</ptxt>
</atten3>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM0000014DK00BX_02" type-id="32" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00007Y800000">
